OL,3,CWho are Hezbollah and why is the group
OL,4,Cinvolved in the Israel-Hamas conflict?
OL,6,FIt has since also become a powerful
OL,7,Fforce in the region with a large
OL,8,Fmilitary, which some say outnumbers
OL,9,FLebanon's own forces.
OL,11,FHezbollah has also become a legitimate
OL,12,Fpart of Lebanese politics, leading to
OL,13,Faccusations that it is a state within
OL,14,Fa state.
OL,16,FThe group currently holds 15 seats in
OL,17,Fthe parliament and is part of the
OL,18,Fseven-party caretaker government.
